verbose_text: GDP/GTP cycling is regulated by guanine nucleotide exchange factors (GEFs) that promote the GDP dissociation and GTP binding, whereas GTPase activating proteins (GAPs) have the opposite effect and stimulate the hydrolysis of Rho-GTP into Rho-GDP.
evidence: GTPase-activating proteins (GAPs) have the opposite effect and stimulate the hydrolysis of Rho-GTP
